item.title: Deobfuscator
item.dc:creator: @fellixombc fellixombc
item.description:
@fellixombc wrote:

[quote=“Natey, post:31, topic:285493”][quote author=fellixombc link=topic=377271.msg2842517#msg2842517 date=1246054147]
Wow, this is probably popcorn39’s deobfuscator. What a deobfuscator does is it turns a runescape client that you downloaded from their website, into a deob, and with a lil bit of editing, and having the cache, you can make the client connect to a private server. Might I add, deobfuscator’s don’t work with today’s client, since this is 2-3 years old.
[/quote]I think it’s Popcorns, you know where I can get a good Deobfuscator for todays?[/quote]
Nowhere that I know of, just use Popcorn’s as a base, and update it, and I doubt anyone will release theirs.

Here are some tutorials that will help though: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,160681.0.html

item.title: Deobfuscator
item.dc:creator: @fellixombc fellixombc
item.description:
@fellixombc wrote:

Wow, this is probably popcorn89’s deobfuscator. What a deobfuscator does is it turns a runescape client that you downloaded from their website, into a deob, and with a lil bit of editing, and having the cache, you can make the client connect to a private server. Might I add, deobfuscator’s don’t work with today’s client, since this is 2-3 years old.

This is basically a Runescape updater, you can fix it with bcel knowledge, and a lot of time, but I doubt anyone would give theirs out, since the last one posted was 2-3 years ago, and it would take time updating.

Bcel tutorial: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,160681.0.html
